Unpack into some directory <dir>

In a new terminal

$ cd <dir>
$ make

This starts the UDP timer server

In Sonic Pi make three buffers

Buffer 0

Buffer0
defonce :osc_sender do
  OSC::UDPClient.new("localhost", 8014)
end

Buffer 1

live_loop :foo do
  info = sync "/play123"
  play 80
end

Buffer 2

osc_sender.send_ts(Time.now+1, "/play123")
osc_sender.send_ts(Time.now+1.1, "/play123")
osc_sender.send_ts(Time.now+1.2, "/play123")
osc_sender.send_ts(Time.now+1.3, "/play123")

Click on Buffer 0 to start a IUDP sender
Click on Buffer 1 to start a cue listener
Click on Buffer 2 to schedule some events



